<paragraph id="8BCE36DAFFE3FFAB24FBFDE5FE4DFBC9" blockId="25.[151,1437,626,1063]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
The plate 
<number id="3DB924FDFFE3FFAB257FFDE5FEBAFD62" box="[275,320,626,652]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" value="674.0">674</number>
of 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE04B2BFFE3FFAB2507FDE5FDD7FD62" author="Garsault" box="[363,557,626,652]" pageId="25" pageNumber="40" refString="Garsault, F. A. P. de (1764) Les Figures des plantes et animaux d'usage en medecine, decrits dans la Matiere Medicale de Mr. Geoffroy Medecin. Paris, [i - v] + 1 - 20, pl. 644 - 729." type="book chapter" year="1764">
Garsault (
<number id="3DB924FDFFE3FFAB2588FDE5FDDEFD62" box="[484,548,626,652]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" value="1764.0">1764</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
shows his species 
<taxonomicName id="4C714D59FFE3FFAB277BFDE4FC0CFD62" authority="Lacepède, 1788" authorityName="Lacepède" authorityYear="1788" box="[791,1014,627,652]" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Lacertus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="aquatilis">
<emphasis id="B905EAC8FFE3FFAB277BFDE4FC0CFD62" box="[791,1014,627,652]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Lacertus aquatilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or “Salamandre d’eau”. The plate provides a good drawing of a breeding male of the newt species currently known (e.g., 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE04B2BFFE3FFAB20FDFD0FFAC1FD5C" author="Raffaelli" box="[1169,1339,664,690]" pageId="25" pageNumber="44" refString="Raffaelli, J. (2007) Les Urodeles du monde. Plumelec, Penclen edition, [i - vi] + 1 - 377." type="book chapter" year="2007">
Raffaëlli 
<number id="3DB924FDFFE3FFAB2092FD0FFAC1FD5C" box="[1278,1339,664,690]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" value="2007.0">2007</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE04B2BFFE3FFAB212BFD0FFE98FD39" author="Dubois" pageId="25" pageNumber="39" refString="Dubois, A. &amp; Raffaelli, J. (2009) A new ergotaxonomy of the family Salamandridae Goldfuss, 1820 (Amphibia, Urodela). Alytes, 26 (1 - 4), 1 - 85." type="journal article" year="2009">
Dubois &amp; Raffaëlli 
<number id="3DB924FDFFE3FFAB2549FD2AFE98FD39" box="[293,354,701,727]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" value="2009.0">2009</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) as 
<taxonomicName id="4C714D59FFE3FFAB25FFFD29FCD0FD39" authority="Laurenti, 1768" authorityName="Laurenti" authorityYear="1768" box="[403,810,701,727]" class="Amphibia" family="Salamandridae" genus="Triturus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Caudata" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cristatus">
<emphasis id="B905EAC8FFE3FFAB25FFFD29FD9AFD39" box="[403,608,702,727]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Triturus cristatus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFE04B2BFFE3FFAB261CFD2AFCDBFD39" author="Laurenti" box="[624,801,701,727]" pageId="25" pageNumber="42" refString="Laurenti, J. N. (1768) Specimen medicum, exhibens synopsin Reptilium emendatam cum experimentis circa venena et antidota Reptilium austriacorum. Viennae, Joan. Thom. Nob. de Trattnern, i - ii + 1 - 215, pl. 1 - 5." type="book chapter" year="1768">
Laurenti, 
<number id="3DB924FDFFE3FFAB2689FD2AFCDBFD39" box="[741,801,701,727]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" value="1768.0">1768</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
(family 
<taxonomicName id="4C714D59FFE3FFAB27FDFD29FAE9FD39" authority="Goldfuss, 1820" authorityName="Goldfuss" authorityYear="1820" box="[913,1299,701,727]" class="Amphibia" family="Salamandridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Caudata" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">
<emphasis id="B905EAC8FFE3FFAB27FDFD29FBABFD39" box="[913,1105,702,727]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">SALAMANDRIDAE</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE04B2BFFE3FFAB2035FD2AFAE9FD39" author="Goldfuss" box="[1113,1299,701,727]" pageId="25" pageNumber="40" refString="Goldfuss, G. A. (1820) Handbuch der Zoologie. Dritter Theil, zweite Abtheilung. Nurnberg, Johann Leonhard Schrag, i - xxiv + 1 - 512, pl. 3 - 4." type="book chapter" year="1820">
Goldfuss, 
<number id="3DB924FDFFE3FFAB20BFFD2AFAE9FD39" box="[1235,1299,701,727]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" value="1820.0">1820</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
). Given the quality of the drawing, showing the dorsal fins on the body and tail, it was most likely drawn from a living specimen, probably from the Paris region, where this subspecies was then common, although nowadays it is rarer there (
<bibRefCitation id="EFE04B2BFFE3FFAB2547FCBAFDB9FCA9" author="Dubois" box="[299,579,813,839]" pageId="25" pageNumber="39" refString="Dubois, A. &amp; Ohler, A. (1988) Expertise batrachologique des mares de Nointel (Val d'Oise). Paris, Societe Batrachologique de France, 1 - 45." type="book chapter" year="1988">
Dubois &amp; Ohler 
<number id="3DB924FDFFE3FFAB266CFCBAFDB9FCA9" box="[512,579,813,839]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" value="1988.0">1988</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). Simply following priority, the species currently known as 
<taxonomicName id="4C714D59FFE3FFAB2154FCB9FEFBFC82" class="Amphibia" family="Salamandridae" genus="Triturus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Caudata" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cristatus">
<emphasis id="B905EAC8FFE3FFAB2154FCB9FEFBFC82" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Triturus cristatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should now be known as 
<taxonomicName id="4C714D59FFE3FFAB262EFCC4FCE3FC82" box="[578,793,851,876]" class="Amphibia" family="Salamandridae" genus="Triturus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Caudata" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="aquatilis">
<emphasis id="B905EAC8FFE3FFAB262EFCC4FCE3FC82" box="[578,793,851,876]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Triturus aquatilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a nomen that has never been used since 
<number id="3DB924FDFFE3FFAB2175FCC5FAA0FC82" box="[1305,1370,850,876]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" value="1764.0">1764</number>
. This change would no doubt be disturbing for communication among zoologists, as since its creation and for almost 
<number id="3DB924FDFFE3FFAB2482FC0AFEE0FC59" box="[238,282,925,951]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" value="200.0">200</number>
years, the nomen 
<taxonomicName id="4C714D59FFE3FFAB2599FC09FD38FC59" box="[501,706,926,951]" class="Amphibia" family="Salamandridae" genus="Triturus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Caudata" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cristatus">
<emphasis id="B905EAC8FFE3FFAB2599FC09FD38FC59" box="[501,706,926,951]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Triturus cristatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been associated with the crested newt of western Europe (for a list of more than 
<number id="3DB924FDFFE3FFAB25CAFC55FE39FC32" box="[422,451,962,988]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" value="25.0">25</number>
recent references, see e.g. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE04B2BFFE3FFAB2693FC55FC59FC32" author="Arntzen" box="[767,931,962,988]" pageId="25" pageNumber="36" refString="Arntzen, J. W. (2003) Triturus cristatus Superspezies - Kammolch-Artenkreis. In: K. Grossenbacher &amp; B. Thiesmeier (ed.), Handbuch der Reptilien und Amphibien Europas, Band 4 / IIA, Wiebelsheim, Aula-Verlag, 421 - 514." type="book chapter" year="2003">
Arntzen 
<number id="3DB924FDFFE3FFAB2708FC55FC59FC32" box="[868,931,962,988]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" value="2003.0">2003</number>
</bibRefCitation>
: 
<number id="3DB924FDFFE3FFAB27C2FC55FBE0FC32" box="[942,1050,962,988]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" value="498.0" valueMax="514.0" valueMin="482.0">482–514</number>
). We therefore use Article 23.9. 
<number id="3DB924FDFFE3FFAB21FEFC55FA66FC32" box="[1426,1436,962,988]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" value="1.0">1</number>
of the 
<emphasis id="B905EAC8FFE3FFAB2489FC7FFEDEFBEF" box="[229,292,1000,1025]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Code</emphasis>
to reject the nomen 
<taxonomicName id="4C714D59FFE3FFAB2671FC7FFC4BFBEC" authority="Garsault, 1764" authorityName="Garsault" authorityYear="1764" box="[541,945,1000,1026]" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Lacertus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="aquatilis">
<emphasis id="B905EAC8FFE3FFAB2671FC7FFD02FBEF" box="[541,760,1000,1025]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Lacertus aquatilis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE04B2BFFE3FFAB276CFC7FFC4BFBEC" author="Garsault" box="[768,945,1000,1026]" pageId="25" pageNumber="40" refString="Garsault, F. A. P. de (1764) Les Figures des plantes et animaux d'usage en medecine, decrits dans la Matiere Medicale de Mr. Geoffroy Medecin. Paris, [i - v] + 1 - 20, pl. 644 - 729." type="book chapter" year="1764">
Garsault, 
<quantity id="4C899B3FFFE3FFAB2719FC7FFC4BFBEC" box="[885,945,1000,1026]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.48056" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" unit="in" value="1764.0">1764</quantity>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
in favour of its junior doxisonym 
<taxonomicName id="4C714D59FFE3FFAB213FFC7FFE48FBC9" authority="Laurenti, 1768" authorityName="Laurenti" authorityYear="1768" genus="Triton" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" rank="species" species="cristatus">
<emphasis id="B905EAC8FFE3FFAB213FFC7FFF06FBC9" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Triton cristatus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE04B2BFFE3FFAB256FFB9AFE48FBC9" author="Laurenti" box="[259,434,1037,1063]" pageId="25" pageNumber="42" refString="Laurenti, J. N. (1768) Specimen medicum, exhibens synopsin Reptilium emendatam cum experimentis circa venena et antidota Reptilium austriacorum. Viennae, Joan. Thom. Nob. de Trattnern, i - ii + 1 - 215, pl. 1 - 5." type="book chapter" year="1768">
Laurenti, 
<number id="3DB924FDFFE3FFAB2518FB9AFE48FBC9" box="[372,434,1037,1063]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" value="1768.0">1768</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
